===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|abundant|lang=enm}}, {{term|habundant|lang=enm}}, {{term|aboundant|lang=enm}}< {{etyl|xno}} {{term|abundant|lang=xno}} < {{etyl|fro}} {{term|abondant|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|abudans|lang=la}}, present participle of {{term|abundo|lang=la}}. See [[abound]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en-us-abundant.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Fully sufficient; found in [[copious]] supply; in great quantity.
#: [W]ith their magical words they [poets] bring forth to our eyesight the '''abundant''' images and beauties of creation. — ''Leigh Hunt, On the Realities of Imagination''
# Richly [[supplied]] — followed by ''in'', rarely by ''with''.
#: '''Abundant''' in goodness and truth. — ''Exodus, 34:6''
# {{mathematics}} Being an [[abundant number]], i.e. less than the sum of all of its [[divisor]]s except itself.

